column5: Are Bass open right now? what zone are you in?
Bass and pike are open year round here..
i see things have not changed much congrats on the outing

how do i put this without sounding cruel or hurtful  you got out fished 5-1  ?  Your Man Card is suspended until further notice ...  IF you cleaned the fish ..cooked it and did the dishes afterwards...  Consider "further notice" to NEVA happen..
OK ok ok....  Bush Chicken........Bet ya can't eat just one  Bush Chicken........It's finger lick'n good  I'd like to acknowledge Colonel Harland Sanders to avoid any copyright infringements
I think you are better at cleaning then catching LEAVE THE FISHING TO THE PRO!!!!!
Ah.. today is another day!!!
It sure is Boss.. but remember the world ends at 6pm tomorrow... so get as much of that Bush Chicken as you can in the next 30 hours!
Irish---you should'nt bait me  Bush Chicken.......Mary Brown serves it up right

Got into camp for the first time.. the original tent didn't fare too well over the winter.. i have a 14x16 to replace it anyway.. this is gonna be TJ's pleasure palace.. lol  Still no leaves here and no bugs yet either!!  anyway got the dock back in and took the ole lady out for a troll..  Fished for an hour and she outfished me 5-1 now i have to listen to that. Kept a couple that were deeply hooked for a snack!! Bass are fantastic this time of year, better than pickerel as far as I'm concerned.. till they get wormy anyway!!  AND.. Bell has installed hispeed all the way to Hearst now, so we now have hi-speed access at camp.. one bar, but it works!!
Enough with the Bird pics, already
Cool deal chief are you wearing blaze orange????  Just askin   Art

OOS Bass?????? That is it, I don't know any TJ (Ok, Ok, so if you send me your Lat. Long. I might not tell!!!!!! See you in about 5 hours! keep the camp fire burning and the pan hot! Come to think of it, you go fishing I'll stay back at camp and keep that lovely lady of your safe from the bears!
Piss off Art, spring season has been closed for years!
"DAMMIT"... you're (can't say that word here) me ! Dang Tootin might work better...  Great get away boss... wish I could drop in and eat your food and snuggle with your wife!
LOL Birds are tasty, and Cliff shell keep you safe.. lol.. i think the rule is if theres no leaves out opening weekend, bass are open.. or something like that.
Looks like a perfect getaway. Nice to get away without the kids, something I need to do badly.
Where's your fish ????? I suppose you just caught the bait for Monique to use to catch hers ?  Or is it your kids using your sign-on again.
Got the same problem here TJ, the wife out fishes me at least 2-1, but man i'm lucky she likes to fish Enjoy the time away.  Paul
Sucks when the wife outfishes ya huh?
So now I got to wait till this fall for my four wheeler.....dangit   Art

That is why they have the man control the bow mounted trolling motor to turn the boat so he's over the fish....at least that's what my bride has been saying for YEARS....not quite sure what she meant though....

Dammit because your in a little slice of heaven, with hi-speed and a fish meal and you're upset the wife outfished you.  Priorities TJ, priorities  Looks great up there, can't believe there are no blackflies yet.  Keep those pics coming bud
So you had partridge and bass for supper, isn't that poaching TJ???
Is there a season on Partridge??    I thought you could eat bush chicken all year long
I'm not a big hunter but i'm pretty sure there's a season for small game. Not sure when it closes but i'm think  the season starts @Sept 15.
Yah.. just googled it Sept 15 to Dec 15.
Wayne just wanted to say "bush chicken" with out getting in trouble...
She doesn't have to out run the bear, just me! I'm old and slow
Your living the good life BOSS.  Dad loved the idea when we were up there that Bass was open all year.  Hope you guys have a great weekend and it stays cool enough to keep them black flies away.
Its not poaching if you eat them raw.
Did Tookie show you how to follow the rules of the outdoors. If so your in big trouble!!
Bush Chicken......It's just not for breakfast anymore
